quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  17,85,"And they will ask you about the spirit. Say, \"The spirit is within my Lord's domain, and you have been given but little knowledge"
  17,86,"And if We so desired, We could easily take away whatever We have revealed to you, and in that [case] you would not find anyone to plead your case with us"
  17,87,"other than mercy from your Lord, His favor towards you is huge"
  17,88,"Say, \"If all people and all Jinn would band together with the intent of generating the likes of this Qur'an, they, would never be able to come out with anything like it, even if they backed each other up"
  17,89,"We have mentioned in this Qur'an every kind of example to benefit people. However, most of the people persist in rejecting the truth"
  17,90,"And so they say, \"We will not believe you [Prophet] until you cause a spring to gush up from the earth"
  17,91,"or, unless you have a garden of dates and grapes and cause rivers to pour through it abundantly"
  17,92,"Or, until the skies fall down upon us-crushing us, as you have threatened to do. Or [until] you bring God and the angels face to face before us"
  17,93,"or, to have a house of gold or you go to heaven-but we would not even believe in your ascension unless you return with a book that we can read! \"Say, \"May my Lord be exalted in His glory, am I other than a man appointed as a messenger"